{
  "texts": [
    "With this data-and compute-efficient approach, we improve instruction-tuned models and two LLM personalization baselines by an average of 40% in the LaMP personalization benchmark (Salemi et al., 2024).",
    "In summary, our contributions are:",
    "We introduce CHAMELEON, an LLM personalization framework that leverages selfgenerated user preference data and embedding editing techniques, providing scalable, user-tailored personalization that is nearly cost-free.",
    "On extensive evaluation using the LaMP benchmark (Salemi et al., 2024), we show that CHAMELEON improves upon instructiontuned models and two LLM personalization benchmarks by an average of 40% on two model architectures.",
    "CHAMELEON can effectively personalize for new, unseen users without user history by leveraging profiles from other users with similar characteristics and preferences."
  ]
}